  ) VALUES (
    'Clean Lift 20/20', 'clean-lift-2020', 'Premium reactive water-based tilt-up Cure/Bondbreaker', 'Désactivateur à base d''eau réactif', 'Antiadherente reactivo en base agua', 'CLEAN LIFT 20/20 is a chemically reactive water based tilt-up cure/bond breaker specifically engineered to provide a clean, easy lift of tilt-up panels and meet the moisture retention of ASTM C309. CLEAN LIFT 20/20 contains no diesel, kerosene, waxes or silicones.

  Easily identifiable on the casting bed
  Clean panels lift easier, no resin stains
  VOC Compliant:  350g/l
  Resists foot traffic abrasion', 'Mix Design: The frequent use of Type II cement and pozzolans (flyash and slag) in casting beds and panel concrete typically slow the rate of hydration, and may delay or reduce bleed making the casting bed and panel concrete more susceptible to drying shrinkage and increase surface porosity at the time of the Clean Lift application. This increased porosity will require an additional cure coat or bondbreaker coat to achieve adequate hold-out prior to pouring panels.

The use of SpecChem "Intrafilm" as a finishing aid will help reduce porosity, and facilitate finishing for denser, tighter slabs.



Curing New Concrete:
Clean Lift 20/20 must be mixed or agitated before each use. Do not dilute. When used as a cure, Clean Lift 20/20 should be applied immediately after the final hard steel troweling at 250-350 sq ft per gal, after the surface water has disappeared. Waiting too long to apply the cure coat can result in porous, dry casting slabs that will not yield favorable results.



Bond Breaker Coat:
Casting slab must be well cured, smooth and dense. Remove all dust, dirt, and other contaminants prior to application. Clean Lift 20/20 should be applied just prior to placing reinforcing steel and within two weeks of pouring panels. Spray apply 300-400 sq ft per gal to the point of rejection. Wait until dry then apply a second coat at right angles to the previous coat. Coverage rate of second coat is typically 500-700 sq ft per gal. Complete uniform coverage is necessary on casting slab. If treated slab appears uneven due to light colored spots, this may indicate a porous slab that requires additional applications of bondbreaker. If after additional applications, these light spots persist, thoroughly wet the affected areas with water to lift concrete pores. Squeegee off excess water and then immediately reapply Clean Lift 20/20. Hold squeegee to thoroughly dry. An adequate application is indicated only by the presence of a dry soap like feel apparent to the touch over the entire treated slab. Do not allow foot traffic until the slab is fully dry.



Bond Breaker Coat on Older/Weather Cured Concrete:
Verify that the concrete surface is free of curing compounds. Remove all laitance that will affect bond breaker performance. Clean Lift 20/20 should be applied to the clean, dense, well cured and clean. Prior to placing reinforcements, spray apply at 300-400 sq ft per gal to the point of rejection. Wait until dry then apply a second coat at right angles to the previous coat.


Squeegee off excess water and immediately apply CLEAN LIFT 20/20 to the point of rejection. Wait until dry and then apply a second coat at right angles to the previous coat. Do not apply additional coats dry. As levels of light colored areas appear after drying, a porous slab may be indicated and reapplication will be necessary. The application rate can vary greatly depending upon the roughness of the slab and the ambient conditions. It is the contractor’s responsibility to ensure the even presence of CLEAN LIFT 20/20 at the surface of the casting slab prior to pouring concrete.



Before Pouring Concrete:
Ensure that the entire treated surface has a dry soap/wax like feel to the touch. Test casting slab by sprinkling a few drops of water in several places. The water should not penetrate and may bead like on a newly waxed car. Fog the entire slab with water prior to pouring. When pouring concrete, avoid scouring the casting slab surface by using a deflection board. Heavy rains or rains prior to bond breaker coats drying may necessitate reapplication.



Stack Panels/Waste slabs:
Extra care must be used with stack panels and waste slabs as they tend to be more porous and can transfer water across their interface increasing the possibility of the “osmotic effect” thus leading to sticking. It is recommended that a SpecChem Cure & Seal or a double coat of bond breaker be applied as the cure coat prior to the bond breaker coat to lessen the chance of sticking.


Please contact SpecChem technical service for special instructions on Casting Slabs or Stack Panels and when using concrete mixes containing pozzolans (slag, fly ash).



Painting of Panels:
If Clean Lift 20/20 has been properly applied and has not been over applied, painting of the panels can be performed as soon as the moisture content in the concrete is at an acceptable level for the paint manufacturer. Coating manufacturer’s instructions for surface preparation must be followed and supersedes information in this data sheet.



Other instructions:
Do not apply in rain or if rain is forecast within 12 hours of application. Panels exposed to rain may require reapplication: 600-700 sq ft per gal. Not recommended for use as a thin breaker on smooth or rough formed surface. Apply for best results with a power sprayer or low pressure sprayer (Chapin, Hudson, etc) with a 1/2 gallon/min tip at a 40 psi pressure stream. Always ensure the complete presence of bond breaker prior to pouring panels.', NULL, NULL, 'Do not allow to freeze! Store material in the original tightly closed containers. Do not allow the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants. Store CLEAN LIFT 20/20 between 45-85 degrees F. Prolonged exposure to high temperatures (above 90 degrees) can significantly reduce shelf-life. Properly stored, shelf-life is 1 year from the date of manufacture.', 'DO NOT ALLOW TO FREEZE. Avoid over applications. CLEAN LIFT 20/20 must be completely dry prior to pouring concrete. Do not walk on bond breaker until completely dry. For best performance, flood the pour area with water immediately before pouring concrete. Do not apply below freezing (32°F).

Important: If the concrete is cured without using a SpecChem cured bond breaker or without a SpecChem ASTM C 309 curing compound, please contact a SpecChem representative for technical support.


DO NOT EXPOSE TO OR APPLY NEAR FIRE OR FLAMES. FOR WELL VENTILATED OR EXTERIOR USE ONLY!', 'Warning', '<p>Stoddard Solvent</p>', 'Causes skin irritation. May cause genetic defects. May cause cancer. May cause respiratory irritation. May cause drowsiness or dizziness. Harmful to aquatic life with long-lasting effects.', 'Wear protective gloves/eye protection/face protection. Wash thoroughly after handling. Obtain special instructions before use. Do not handle until all safety precautions have been read and understood. Avoid breathing dust/fume/gas/mist/vapors/spray. Use only outdoors or in a well-ventilated area. Avoid release to the environment.', NULL, 'If on skin: Wash with water. If inhaled: Remove person to fresh air. If exposed or concerned: Get medical attention.', 'Store in a well-ventilated place. Keep cool.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', NULL, 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'VOC Compliant < 350g/l',
