    green_conscious, do_not_freeze, mix_well, used_by_date, subtitle_1, subtitle_2, voc_data,
    category_id, sort_order, is_active
  ) VALUES (
    'Poly Fix (Part A)', 'poly-fix-part-a', 'Ultra-Low Viscosity Polymer Concrete Repair Binder', 'Liant de réparation de béton polymère à viscosité ultra-faible', 'Ligante de reparación de concreto con polímero de ultra baja viscosidad', 'Poly Fix® is a high-strength, two-component ultra-low viscosity hybrid polyurethane concrete repair binder. Poly Fix® can be used to penetrate hairline cracks or mixed with dry sand to patch/repair concrete spalls or control joints. Poly Fix®’s water-like consistency also makes it an excellent crack healer/sealer for deteriorated concrete surfaces. Poly Fix® contains low VOC’s.
Primary Applications for Poly Fix® are:
- Bridge Decks/Parking Decks
- Auto/truck repair bays
- Concrete crack healer/sealer
- Concrete subjected to mild chemical attack
- Anchoring bolts, railings, equipment
- Floor restoration projects
- Repairing spalls and pop-outs
- Repairs freezer floors down to 0°F', 'Surface Preparation: All concrete to be repaired must be clean, dry and sound. New Concrete must be a minimum of 30 days old. All contaminants, oil, debris, coatings and unsound concrete must be removed.


Cracks should be prepared with a crack chaser, dry diamond blade, wet wheel on a hand grinder or a vacuum blast method. For surface patching applications hot and cold joints properly prepared with a crack chasing hammer, needle gun or diamond grinder. 4” large diameter bits conform to ICRI CSP 5-7 should be used. All spalls and patch areas require that heavy loose or unsound concrete be removed to a depth of at least 1/8”.


Cartridge Mixing: Poly Fix® should be conditioned to a temperature of 60°F to 80°F. Thoroughly shake the cartridge for 30 sec to mix each component. Remove the cap and holding upright, attach the flow restrictor to the cartridge then the static mixer with nut. Insert into dual cartridge and point the static mixer into a waste receptacle and dispense 4-5 inches of material to ensure proper mix. Once dispensing has started, do not turn upright to prevent backflow. Immediately apply the mixed product to the repair area.
Bulk Mixing: Poly Fix® is a very rapid-setting product. Therefore larger bulk mix units (2gal & 1gal) should be mixed in quart batches. Mix 1 pint Part A with 1 pint Part B for 30 sec then add up to 2 quarts of dry sand or use SpecPoxy Mortar Part C, mix for an additional 15 sec and immediately place into the prepared repair area.
Placement: For cracks or patching repairs greater than 3/4" wide. Pre-wet the area with Poly Fix® and fill with coarse dry sand (16/40) or use SpecPoxy Mortar Part C to the proper elevation. Immediately saturate the sand with Poly Fix® resin, allowing to saturate the sand by means of the primed substrate. Apply additional sand if necessary while the resin fills and binds to the level of the surface. As Poly Fix® cures, the resin dries and hardens with full bearing. If necessary, sanding, grinding or polishing can begin 1-3 hours after initial cure.
Low Temperature Repairs: Condition Poly Fix® and any other materials (sand) to 70°F before mixing and applying in areas subject to cold. Cure time will be extended depending on the application area.', '- Easy 1 to 1 mix ratio
- Penetrates concrete to seal against liquid absorption
- Rapid installation saves time and labor
- Dark amber color when mixed, dries gray
- Cures in 10 min @ 75°F
- Structurally restores concrete surfaces
- Tough permanent repairs
- VOC compliant (0 VOC’s)', '1 gallon of Poly Fix® when mixed with 2 gallons of dry 16/40 sand will yield approximately 2.2 gallons of durable polymer concrete. Coverage rate depends on the porosity of the concrete.', 'Store Poly Fix® in its original containers and keep tightly closed. Do Not Allow to Freeze! Do not allow any moisture or the accumulation of water, dirt or other contaminants. The shelf life of properly stored Poly Fix® is 9 months from date of manufacture.', '- Poly Fix® must be thoroughly mixed to completely disperse the pigment. This is especially important with the cartridges. Improper mixing/pigment dispersion may result in a white appearance for the cured Poly Fix®
- Poly Fix® is a rigid material and should not be used in moving cracks or joints
- Only apply to concrete free of moisture
- Store indoors at 45°F to 90°F
- Product may discolor in outdoor (strong sunlight) environments
- When using a cartridge, do not hold vertical after pumping to prevent backflow into the cartridge. If material hardens in the mixer, detach and replace with new mixer
- Components may cause irritation. Avoid contact with eyes and skin
- Apply only over dry concrete surfaces
- If HVAC intake ducts will distribute odor into adjoining occupied areas of the building, care should be taken to block these ventilation vents.


DO NOT EXPOSE TO OR APPLY NEAR FIRE OR FLAMES. FOR WELL VENTILATED INTERIOR OR EXTERIOR USE ONLY!', 'Danger', '4,4’-Methylenediphenyl diisocyanate (50-70%), Benzene, 1,1’-methylenebis [isocyanato-, homopolymer] (10-30%), Diphenylmethane-2,4’-diisocyanate (5-10%), and 2,2,4-trimethyl-1,3-pentanediol diisobutyrate in concentrations less than 40%.', 'This product is an irritant and may cause skin, eye, and respiratory irritation. It is a sensitizer and may cause allergic skin or respiratory reactions. It is classified as a carcinogen (Category 2) and is suspected of causing cancer. It also has reproductive toxicity (Category 2) and is suspected of damaging the unborn child. There is an aspiration hazard and it may cause drowsiness or dizziness if inhaled.', 'You should avoid breathing vapors, dust, or mist. Use this product only outdoors or in well-ventilated areas. Always wear protective gloves, clothing, and both eye and face protection. Wash thoroughly after handling the material. Store the product locked up in original unopened containers, between 60°F and 80°F (15–27°C), away from sunlight and moisture.', 'If inhaled, move the person to fresh air and administer oxygen if necessary. If the product comes in contact with the eyes, rinse immediately with water for at least 15 minutes and seek medical attention. If skin contact occurs, wash with soap and water and remove contaminated clothing. If ingested, do not induce vomiting and seek medical advice.', 'If inhaled, move the person to fresh air and administer oxygen if necessary. If the product comes in contact with the eyes, rinse immediately with water for at least 15 minutes and seek medical attention. If skin contact occurs, wash with soap and water and remove contaminated clothing. If ingested, do not induce vomiting and seek medical advice.', NULL, 'Dispose of the contents and container according to local, state, and federal regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable.<br>

In containers of 119 gallons or less this product is not regulated by DOT. Shipments in containers of more than 119 gallons, this product is regulated by DOT and must ship as flammable liquid.', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4', NULL, '1 Year', NULL, NULL, 'VOC compliant (0 VOC’s)',
