    'SpecPlug MKS', 'specplug-mks', 'Polymer-modified, fiber-reinforced concrete repair mortar', 'Mortier de réparation de béton modifié aux polymères et renforcé de fibres', 'Mortero de reparación de concreto modificado con polímeros y reforzado con fibra', 'SpecPlug is a durable, fast-setting hydraulic-cement mortar that stops flowing water through holes and cracks in concrete and masonry surfaces. SpecPlug will not shrink or oxidize.', 'Recommended for use in:- Swimming pools- Sewer pipes- Manholes- Tunnels- Below-grade foundations- Basement and masonry cracks- Floor and wall jointsSurface Preparation: For best results, enlarge cracks to a width and depth of 3/4" (19 mm); cut square or undercut. Do not cut in a “V” shape. Clean the substrate of all grease, wax, oil, contaminants, and curing compounds. Remove all weak, contaminated, or deteriorated concrete. Saturate the surface with water. SpecPlug will cure in the presence of running water.Mixing: Add a small amount of clean water to SpecPlug and mix to a putty consistency. Use an approximate ratio of 20% – 21% water to product (by weight). Mix only enough material that can be placed in 2 minutes: approximately 9.5 pints water to 50 lbs of product.Application: For vertical and moving-water applications, hold the product firmly in place until it reaches final set. Use hot water and warm material to speed setting time if temperatures are below 60°F (16°C). In temperatures above 80°F (27°C), protect the material from the hot sun and use cold water to slow the setting time.Curing: SpecPlug cures and continues to gain strength as long as it remains damp. Keep the material damp for a minimum of 30 minutes. The product achieves optimal strength when wet cured for up to 2 days.
