  ) VALUES (
    'Concrete Cure w/Dye', 'concrete-cure-wdye', 'Sodium silicate cure & dustproofer', 'Durcisseur et anti-poussière au silicate de sodium', 'Agente de curado y antipolvo a base de silicato de sodio', 'CONCRETE CURE is a spray applied concrete cure, hardener and dustproofer. CONCRETE CURE deeply penetrates concrete surfaces to densify, seal, harden and dustproof concrete and Portland Cement based material surfaces to help them achieve maximum abrasion resistance and without altering the natural appearance of the concrete. May contribute to LEED credits. Available with and without fugitive dye.

  Economical, non flammable and ready to use
  Does not alter natural color of aggregate or concrete
  Actual VOC = 0g/l, odorless
  Helps seal concrete against acids, oils, greases, salts and tire marks
  Will not inhibit the adhesion of secondary toppings, adhesives, or coatings designed for concrete', 'COVERAGE
Curing, sealing, hardening and dustproofing:

  Hard Troweled Finish: 300-500 sq ft / gal
  Broom or Float Finish: 200-400 sq ft / gal
  Rough Finish: 200-300 sq ft / gal
  Aged Concrete: 200-300 sq ft / gal
  Vertical Surface: 200-300 sq ft / gal

The above rates are approximate. Exact coverage depends upon the porosity of the concrete and finishing requirements. For optimum hardening of porous surfaces, apply two coats.


Apply immediately after final finishing operations and after the bleed water has receded. Brush out puddles and runs. Over application and puddling will leave white crystals, which must be removed by immediately flushing the surface with water and scrubbing.


May be applied with sprayer, brush or roller. Spraying provides superior results.


Application temperatures 40°F to 100°F.


Protect metal, glass, painted and brick surfaces from CONCRETE CURE. If accidentally misapplied, wash with clean water at once.


For aged concrete, surface must be free of dirt and all other foreign matter. Surface should be dry to permit maximum penetration.


As jobsite conditions vary, a test panel should always be performed.', NULL, NULL, 'When stored in the original, tightly closed container, preventing the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants, the shelf life is two years from the date of manufacture. Do not allow to freeze.', 'Protect from freezing. If the surface is to be treated with glue, coating, or paint, excess CONCRETE CURE residue must be completely removed. Avoid contact with glass, aluminum, or other glazed or finished surfaces. Where contact has occurred, immediately wipe with a damp cloth or flush with water. Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Danger', 'Sodium Silicate', 'Harmful if swallowed. Causes severe skin burns.', 'Do not breathe dust or mist. Wash skin thoroughly after handling. Do not eat, drink, or smoke when using this product. Wear protective gloves/protective clothing/eye protection/face protection.', NULL, 'If swallowed: Rinse mouth, do not induce vomiting. If on skin: Remove contaminated clothing and rinse with water. If inhaled: Remove person to fresh air.', 'Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, 'Actual VOC = 0g/l',
