  ) VALUES (
    'Crete-Away', 'crete-away', 'Water-based biodegradable concrete remover', 'Dissolvant de béton biodégradable à base d''eau', 'Removedor de concreto biodegradable a base de agua', 'A chemically active liquid formulated to soften and remove concrete build up from concrete tools and equipment. CRETE-AWAY® is designed to help avoid the damaging effects of sandblasting, bushhammering and jackhammering hardened concrete from equipment.', 'Brush or spray apply ready-to-use CRETE-AWAY® to the hardened concrete surface or mortar to be removed at approximately 75 ft²/gal (1.8 m²/gal). If possible, immersion is the best application method. A light foaming action may occur. Allow product to soak and agitate.


After the concrete has softened, re-apply an additional application and allow this to remain on the surface for approximately 10-15 minutes, then remove softened concrete with a stiff brush or plastic scraper. In difficult cases, subsequent applications may be necessary. The final application may be removed with water. Deposits more than 1/4" (6 mm) may require multiple applications.


If adequate deposits resist prior to removal, apply additional CRETE-AWAY® as needed. Leave the fresh application on for 10-15 minutes, then remove softened concrete with a stiff brush or scraper.', 'Ready-to-use - No mixing required.

  Bio-degradable, non-corrosive, low-odor, water based, won’t contaminate ground water.

  Reduces labor costs and equipment damage normally associated with removing built up, hardened concrete.

  Prevents damage to equipment caused by physical removal such as sandblasting or hammering.

  V.O.C. compliant.

  Will not harm most painted metal surfaces (i.e., automobiles).

  Dissolves concrete and mortar on tools, equipment and forms.

  Safely etches concrete floors.', NULL, 'Shelf life of CRETE-AWAY® in the original tightly closed container is 2 years from the date of manufacture. Do not allow the accumulation of water, dirt or other contaminants. Do not allow this product to freeze.', 'Though CRETE-AWAY® is relatively safe to use, always wear protective clothing (rubber gloves, eye protection, etc.)

  Do not dilute. Diluting CRETE-AWAY® will greatly diminish its effectiveness.

  CRETE-AWAY® contains a mild organic acid which may oxidize certain metals if left in contact for long periods of time. After the concrete has been removed, thoroughly flush the area with clean water.

  Concrete surfaces must be dry before applying CRETE-AWAY®.

  Do not allow this product to freeze.

  Cold weather reduces the effectiveness of CRETE-AWAY®.

  A small area should be tested to ensure against staining of new equipment surfaces.', 'Danger', 'Glycolic Acid', 'Harmful if swallowed. Causes severe skin burns. Causes serious eye damage.', 'Do not breathe dust or mist. Wash skin thoroughly after handling. Do not eat, drink, or smoke when using this product. Wear protective gloves/protective clothing/eye protection/face protection.', NULL, 'If swallowed: Call poison center/doctor. If on skin: Rinse with water and remove contaminated clothing. If in eyes: Rinse with water and remove contact lenses if present. Seek medical attention.', 'Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Acetic Acid Solution (10-50%)', 'UN2790', 'Class 8 - Corrosive', 'PG III', '153', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, NULL,
