    'Form Seasoning WB', 'form-seasoning-wb', 'Water-based treatment for new aluminum forms', 'Traitement à base d''eau pour formes en aluminium neuves', 'Tratamiento a base de agua para formaletas nuevas de aluminio', 'Form Seasoning WB is a water-based treatment for new aluminum forms. It oxidizes the elemental aluminum on the surface of new aluminum forms to properly season and prepare them for use. Once seasoned, use a quality reactive form release agent to produce a clean release. Properly seasoned aluminum forms are required to reduce sticking that can take place between aluminum and fresh concrete.
Actual/Maximum VOC content = 0 grams per liter.', 'Ready to use. Do not dilute. Mix well prior to each use. Forms should be free from dirt, hardened concrete, or other foreign matter. Form Seasoning WB can be used at temperatures as low as 40°F, but best results are achieved if air and form temperatures are above 70°F.Form Seasoning WB can be applied with a sprayer, roller, or brush. Spray product on side rails while forms are still in stacks. Lay forms on the ground, face up. Apply Form Seasoning WB to the point of rejection, typically 300 sq ft/gal. Uniform bubbling on the form surface indicates that the product is properly reacting with the aluminum. Average reaction time is 30 minutes to 1 hour depending on the form temperature. Do not allow Form Seasoning WB to dry on the form; lightly mist with water or more Form Seasoning WB if necessary.Remove the product with a hose or low-pressure (100 psi or lower) sprayer. Do not use a high-pressure washer as the newly formed oxides on the form surface can be disturbed. Once dry, the oxides will be bonded to the surface. Forms will be dull and almost gray in color. If shiny areas are still present, a second application will be necessary. Allow forms to dry. Once dry, use a quality reactive release agent to achieve a clean release. Apply at 300 sq ft/gal to ensure proper seasoning of forms.', NULL, NULL, 'When stored in the original, tightly closed container, preventing the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants, the shelf life is one year from the date of manufacture.', 'PROTECT FROM FREEZING. FOR INDUSTRIAL USE ONLY. USE ONLY WITH ADEQUATE VENTILATION. AVOID SKIN CONTACT; PG II CORROSIVE LIQUIDS, n.o.s. UN1824 (contains sodium hydroxide). Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Danger', 'Caustic Soda', 'H314 Causes severe skin burns and eye damage.', 'P260 Do not breathe dust or mists. P264 Wash skin thoroughly after handling. P270 Do not eat, drink or smoke when using this product. P280 Wear protective gloves/ protective clothing/ eye protection/ face protection.', 'P301+P330+P331 IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. Do NOT induce vomiting. P303+P361+P353 IF ON SKIN (or hair): Take off immediately all contaminated clothing. Rinse skin with water/shower. P363 Wash contaminated clothing before reuse. P304+P340 IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing. P310 Immediately call a POISON CENTER/doctor. P321 Specific treatment - see supplemental first aid instruction. P305+P351+P338 IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing.', 'P301+P330+P331 IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. Do NOT induce vomiting. P303+P361+P353 IF ON SKIN (or hair): Take off immediately all contaminated clothing. Rinse skin with water/shower. P363 Wash contaminated clothing before reuse. P304+P340 IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing. P310 Immediately call a POISON CENTER/doctor. P321 Specific treatment - see supplemental first aid instruction. P305+P351+P338 IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing.', 'P405 Store locked up.', 'P501 Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Sodium Hydroxide Solution', 'Class 8 – Corrosive', 'PGII', '154', 'Corrosive', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', NULL, NULL, '1 year', NULL, NULL, NULL,
