  ) VALUES (
    'IntraFilm Concentrate', 'intrafilm-concentrate', 'Concentrated colloidal silica densifier and finishing aid', 'Concentré de densifiant à base de silice colloïdale réactive et aide à la finition', 'Concentrado de densificador de sílice coloidal y ayuda de acabado', 'INTRAFILM CONCENTRATE is a reactive colloidal silica densifier and finishing aid that, when diluted with potable water at 1 to 1, fortifies freshly placed concrete for faster and easier finishing and prolonged workability in adverse conditions, such as high temperatures, high wind or low humidity. The reactive colloidal silica in INTRAFILM reacts with calcium hydroxide to create slabs with higher densification, less dusting, and lower maintenance requirements.', 'INTRAFILM is designed for use during the floating and troweling stages of concrete placement. Use a clean, hand-pump tank-type sprayer with a low-pressure tip to distribute the product evenly. Lightly mist INTRAFILM over entire surface to be treated and immediately follow with screeding, floating, troweling, or other finishing procedures. INTRAFILM can also be applied after finishing as a curing aid or broom-finish. Reapply INTRAFILM to any localized areas where the concrete has begun to dry prematurely. Can also be applied both before and after dry-shake hardeners to allow surface moisture time to wet out dryshakes.


MIXING INSTRUCTIONS

INTRAFILM CONCENTRATE must be diluted with water. Contents should be stirred or shaken vigorously prior to use to eliminate any settling which may occur upon storage or shipping. The concentrate should be diluted by mixing 1-part concentrate to 4-parts clean, potable water and shake or stir until mixture is uniform. Pour diluted INTRAFILM directly into sprayer.', NULL, 'Surface Coverage based on ready-to-use formula:



  Finishing Aid: 500 to 1000 square feet per gallon

  Concrete Densifier: 200 square feet per gallon



Coverage rates are provided as a guideline only. Many variables, including surface profile and porosity, will determine actual coverage rates.', 'Shelf life of INTRAFILM CONCENTRATE in the original tightly closed containers is two years from the date of manufacture.', 'KEEP FROM FREEZING.

  INTRAFILM does not replace curing procedures.

  Do not store below 40°F or above 80°F (26.7°C).

  Do not stand or puddle on the surface. Over application will increase the time and bring clouding/haziness to the finish.

  Use a reduced 250 sq-ft/gal when applying multiple items or in combination with other colloidal silica treatments.', 'Danger', 'Sodium Silicate N', 'Harmful if swallowed. Causes severe skin burns.', 'Do not breathe dust or mist. Wash skin thoroughly after handling. Do not eat, drink, or smoke when using this product. Wear protective gloves/protective clothing/eye protection/face protection.', NULL, 'If swallowed, rinse mouth and seek medical advice. If in eyes, rinse cautiously with water for 15 minutes. Call Poison Control if necessary.', 'Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not regulated', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, NULL,
