  ) VALUES (
    'LithSeal SG', 'lithseal-sg', 'High sheen concrete protectant and burnishing aid', 'Protecteur de béton à haute brillance et aide au brunissage', 'Protector de hormigón de alto brillo y ayudante de pulido', 'LithSeal SG is a water-based polymeric sealer/densifier combined with a blend of reactive lithium silicates to protect and improve the appearance of concrete floors. LithSeal SG incorporates a cross-linking nano-technology that aids penetration and adhesion, creating a tough, stain-resistant coating. LithSeal SG also contains UV absorbers that enable it to protect colored or dyed concrete against UV degradation. LithSeal SG can be used alone or in combination with other reactive sealer/densifiers such as SpecHard or LithSeal SC to give concrete floors a glossy finish, harder surface, and protective chemically resistant seal.', 'Always apply LithSeal SG to a clean surface free of cures, bond breakers, oil, dirt, grease, or debris. Clean concrete surfaces with SpecChem Orange Peel Citrus Cleaner and neutralize with a neutral pH detergent. Thoroughly flush with water. LithSeal SG is designed to be applied at the provided concentration. Do not dilute or alter. LithSeal SG may be applied to steel troweled, honed, polished, or highly polished concrete surfaces.**Before Applying LithSeal SG**:1. Lightly wet a clean microfiber pad with LithSeal SG and wring out excess, leaving the pad damp.2. Working from one control joint to another, apply a light, fine spray of LithSeal SG to a small section of the floor using a clean pump-up sprayer fitted with a 0.5 gpm spray tip.3. Using the damp microfiber pad and firm downward pressure, immediately spread the LithSeal SG to produce a thin, even coating. Spread the product as far as possible while maintaining a wet edge. Properly applied, LithSeal SG dries quickly. Stop spreading once drying begins. Avoid overlapping.4. Allow drying to be tack-free, typically 20-60 minutes.5. Once dry, burnish LithSeal SG using a high-speed burnisher fitted with a burnishing pad or equivalent. Polishing the treated surface and high-speed burnishing heats the LithSeal SG to help the treatment fuse and bond with the concrete for increased durability and longevity.6. Repeat steps 1-5 above as necessary for the desired finish. Burnish between coats. Apply up to three coats for maximum gloss. Coverage rates will vary with concrete porosity: - Fresh, Uncured, Burnished Concrete: 600-1000 ft²/gal - Existing Steel Troweled Concrete: 400-500 ft²/gal - Existing Float Finished Concrete: 250-350 ft²/gal', NULL, NULL, 'When stored in the original, tightly closed container, preventing the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants, the shelf life is one year from the date of manufacture.', 'As every project and application can vary, it is the contractor’s responsibility to determine compatibility by performing field tests simulating actual jobsite conditions. Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Warning', 'Lithium Silicate', 'Causes serious eye irritation.', 'Wash thoroughly after handling. Wear eye protection/face protection.', NULL, 'If in eyes, rinse cautiously with water. Seek medical attention if irritation persists.', 'None applicable.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not regulated', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', NULL, NULL, '1 year', NULL, NULL, 'VOC Content = < 50 g/l',
