  ) VALUES (
    'MVM Prime 5000 (Part A)', 'mvm-prime-5000-part-a', '100% solids epoxy moisture barrier system', 'Système de barrière d''humidité à l''époxy 100% solide', 'Sistema de barrera de humedad de epoxy al 100% de sólidos', 'MVM PRIME 5000 is a 2-component, 100% solids epoxy moisture barrier system designed to effectively stop moisture vapor related problems on concrete prior to installing SpecChem underlayments or overlayment. MVM PRIME 5000 also provides an excellent bond to concrete and can be applied to concrete as early as 5 days old where early application of floor covering is required.
Actual VOC =0 grams per liter', 'Concrete Surface Preparation: New Concrete must cure minimum of 5 days with oil and all curing compounds and sealers removed. Concrete must meet minimum tensile strength of 150 psi. The concrete must be prepared by diamond grinding. All oil, dirt, debris, paint and unsound concrete must be removed. The concrete surface must be prepared using mechanical methods shotblasts to a minimum ICRI Concrete Surface Profile of 3 (CSP #3). Acid etching is not acceptable. SpecChem cannot be responsible for variations in slab design, preparation, isolation or moving joints resulting from dry up, delowage, shrink or cracking after installation of vapor barrier system.


Recommended Tools: Epoxy mixing paddle, low speed drill, paint roller, squeegee, brush, or mechanical spray. All application equipment should be clean and free of contaminants prior to mixing or application.


MIXING

All materials should be acclimated to the application temperature range of 65°F to 85°F. Mix parts together as follows:
1. Open Part B hardener container and pour into the epoxy resin container labeled Part A. Add 1 - Part B to 2 - Parts A by volume.
2. Mix together for 3 minutes. Once mixed, pour some of the epoxy back into the hardener container, mix for an additional minute, then pour all the material back into the resin container, ensuring the hardener and resin are fully blended.
3. Continue mixing until no streaks remain and product is uniform. Use immediately after mixing. The epoxy must be mixed to ensure proper chemical reaction. After mixing, place immediately on the prepared surface.', 'One-Coat epoxy system
Easy to spread/excellent coverage
VOC Compliant, VOC = 0 grams/liter
Reduces moisture vapor for floor coverings
ASTM E 96 - 0.6 perms @ 14 mils
Excellent bond strength to concrete', NULL, 'The shelf life of properly stored MVM PRIME 5000 is two years from date of batch. Do not expose to freezing. Keep away from heat and sun. Store in a cool dry place. Keep container tightly closed when not in use. Do not store below 40°F or above 80°F. Keep away from open flames.', 'Do not allow exposure to water or liquids before curing is complete. SpecChem cannot be responsible for cracks or movement of the substrate that affect the epoxy.', 'Warning', 'Bisphenol A Diglycidyl Ether Resin, Glycidyl 2-methylphenyl Ether', 'Causes skin irritation. May cause an allergic skin reaction. Causes serious eye irritation. Suspected of causing genetic defects. Toxic to aquatic life with long-lasting effects.', 'Wear protective gloves, eye protection, and face protection. Wash thoroughly after handling. Avoid breathing dust, fumes, gas, mist, vapors, or spray. Contaminated clothing should not be allowed out of the workplace. Avoid release into the environment.', 'IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. DO NOT induce vomiting. IF ON SKIN (or hair): Remove/take off immediately all contaminated clothing. Rinse skin with water/shower. IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing. IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing. Immediately call a POISON CENTER or doctor/physician. If skin irritation or rash occurs: Get medical advice/attention. Take off contaminated clothing and wash before reuse.', 'IF SWALLOWED: Rinse mouth. DO NOT induce vomiting. IF ON SKIN (or hair): Remove/take off immediately all contaminated clothing. Rinse skin with water/shower. IF INHALED: Remove person to fresh air and keep comfortable for breathing. IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing. Immediately call a POISON CENTER or doctor/physician. If skin irritation or rash occurs: Get medical advice/attention. Take off contaminated clothing and wash before reuse.', 'Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not regulated', NULL, 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, 'VOC = 0 grams/liter',
