    'Plaster Bond', 'plaster-bond', 'Rewettable Bonding Agent', 'Agent de liaison réhumidifiable', 'Agente de unión rehumectable', 'PLASTER BOND is a rewettable PVA latex bonding agent designed especially for interior/exterior bonding of fresh plaster in patching, plastering and topping applications. Recommended for interior and exterior use for substrates not subjected to constant moisture, hydrostatic pressure or continuous water saturation. Can be used as an admixture to improve the adhesion and durability of interior plaster and plaster mixes to horizontal and vertical surfaces. May contribute to LEED credits.', 'Surface Preparation: Mechanically abrade existing substrate to remove all unsound concrete. Substrate must be structurally sound and free of all foreign, grease, oil, dirt or any other contaminants that may adversely affect the bond. Prepared surfaces must be dust-free and must have sufficient profile to ensure adequate mechanical lock.  Mixing and Application Guidelines: Agitate well before use.  Bonding Agent: Apply a uniform coating of undiluted PLASTER BOND at 250 sq.ft per gallon to the prepared substrate by brush, roller or sprayer. If spray applied, brush or broom into the substrate to ensure an even film over the entire area to be bonded. The open time will be when the product dries to the touch. Dry time is 20-30 min at 70°F. PLASTER BOND will remain slightly tacky when dry. Accumulation in low areas should be wiped or evenly distributed for uniform dry time. This will help prevent over-application to speed drying time. Under normal conditions, PLASTER BOND can be applied up to 24 hours before installation of plaster/adhesional toppings. All materials should be kept to a minimum.  Rewettable Applications: For rewettable applications of PLASTER BOND: Always re-tackify the bonding agent with a water mist if a continuous film is not achieved on the surface, reapply PLASTER BOND.  Place plaster or stucco within 24 hours of application.  The application instructions highlight typical conditions. (When in doubt, always apply a test patch.)   Application Rate: 250 sq.ft per gal depending on the roughness/porosity of the substrate.', 'Excellent Bond Strength High viscosity for optimum performance Improves the flexural strength, bond strength and impact resistance of plaster, and stucco mortars to concrete Minimizes cracks in interior, stucco and plaster when used as an admixture VOC compliant. VOC content: &lt; 50 g/l Blue tint for visual inspection (also available in white)', NULL, 'Shelf life of PLASTER BOND in the original tightly closed container is 1 year from the date of manufacture. Protect from freezing. Do not allow the accumulation of water, dirt or other contaminants.', 'Do not allow to freeze. Do not apply to frozen substrates, over stable paints, rust or peeling paints or whenever temperature is below 40°F. Do not use in areas subject to constant moisture, hydrostatic pressure or continuous water saturation. PLASTER BOND is not recommended as a waterproofing or vapor barrier. Apply in accordance with all safety information and first aid contained in the Material Safety Data Sheet (SDS), product labels and technical literature.', NULL, NULL, 'This material is not hazardous under the criteria of the Federal OSHA Hazard Communication Standard 29CFR 1910.1200.', '• Avoid contact with eyes, skin and clothing. • Wash thoroughly after handling. • Keep container tightly closed. • Do not breathe vapors, mist or gas. • Use personal protective equipment. • Use local exhaust ventilation with a minimum capture velocity of 100 ft/min (0.5 m/sec) at the point of vapor evolution. • Facilities storing or utilizing this material should be equipped with an eyewash facility. • Eye/face protection: Safety glasses with side-shields. • Hand protection: Neoprene gloves. • Respiratory protection: Not required under normal operating conditions. Where vapors and/or mists may occur, wear a properly fitted NIOSH approved (or equivalent) half-mask, air purifying respirator with organic vapor cartridges and N95 filters.', NULL, NULL, '• Keep from freezing—product stability may be affected. • Stir well before use. • Store tightly closed at 1–49°C (34–120°F).', '• Coagulate the emulsion by the stepwise addition of ferric chloride and lime. • Remove the clear supernatant and flush to a chemical sewer. • For disposal, incinerate or landfill at a permitted facility in accordance with local, state, and federal regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'VOC content: < 50 g/l. VOC compliant.',
