    'Sealer Renew', 'sealer-renew', 'High-strength Deblushing Solvent/Cleaner', 'Solvant/nettoyant déblanchissant à haute résistance', 'Solvente/limpiador de alta resistencia para eliminar el blanqueo', 'A specially blended high-strength solvent formulated to brighten and rejuvenate existing decorative acrylic sealers. Sealer ReNew can also be used to clean or strip deteriorated sealer and to release moisture blush (whitening) trapped beneath the sealer. Sealer ReNew provides an economical and practical alternative to applying additional coats of sealer year after year.', 'General preparation: Since the Sealer ReNew evaporates quickly, surfaces to be treated should be addressed in small areas (5’ x 5’) and best in cool temperatures with minimal direct sunlight. Remove any dirt or contaminants that will prevent the Sealer ReNew from coming in direct contact with the old sealer.
Renewing old sealer: Brush or spray apply at approximately 250-300 sq. ft per gal and allow to penetrate the old sealer for 3-4 minutes. In areas of severe whitening (moisture blush) agitate the surface with a cloth rag or paint brush to release the moisture and dissolve the discoloration. Once the cured sealer has been treated, allow to dry.
