    'SpecPlate', 'specplate', 'Metallic Floor Topping', 'Chape de sol métallique', 'Revestimiento metálico para pisos', 'SpecPlate Floor Hardener is a metallic dry-shake hardener designed to provide superior abrasion resistance and durability for interior concrete floors. SpecPlate Floor Hardener is ideal for industrial environments subjected to heavy traffic and abrasion. It is applied during the concrete finishing process to become an integral part of the surface, providing long-lasting protection.', 'Surface Preparation: Ensure the surface is clean, free of contaminants, and properly prepared according to ACI guidelines. Apply a bond coat of SpecPoxy 1000, ensuring complete coverage.Placing: Once the concrete is placed, screeded, tamped, and floated, apply the first 2/3 of the SpecPlate Floor Hardener coverage, allowing it to absorb moisture from the slab. Float the material into the surface using a bull float or power trowel. Apply the remaining 1/3 of the hardener, float again, and finish the surface using a power trowel. Ensure the hardener is fully integrated into the top surface of the slab.Finishing: After the surface has sufficiently stiffened, apply SpecFilm as a finishing aid and continue troweling. Use a hard troweled surface for maximum durability. Do not add water to aid in finishing.Curing: Apply an ASTM C-309 compliant curing compound after final troweling.
SCAQMD Rule 1113 compliant', NULL, NULL, 'Shelf life of unopened bags stored in a dry facility is 12 months. Excessive temperature differential and high humidity can shorten the shelf life. Store in a cool, dry area away from direct sunlight.', 'Do not place at temperatures below 40°F (5°C) or if the temperature is expected to fall below 40°F (5°C) within the next 24 hours. Avoid the use of dry-shake hardeners where floors will be exposed to acids or chemicals that attack Portland cement. Do not exceed a slump of 4” (10.16 cm). Avoid air entrainment in the concrete, ensuring that total air content does not exceed 3%. Do not use calcium chloride or aggregates contaminated by saltwater.Caution: Contains Portland cement and sand. Avoid contact with skin and eyes. Use a dust respirator, safety goggles, and rubber gloves. In case of eye contact, flush with water for 15 minutes and seek medical attention. Do not take internally. Keep out of reach of children. Follow all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheet (SDS).', 'Danger', '<p>Crystalline Silica, Portland Cement, Calcium Oxide, Aluminum Sulfate</p>', 'Obtain special instructions before use. Do not handle until all safety precautions have been read and understood. Do not breathe dust/fumes/mist/vapors/spray. Wash thoroughly after handling. Use only outdoors or in a well-ventilated area. Contaminated work clothing should not be allowed out of the workplace. Do not eat, drink, or smoke when using this product. Wear protective gloves, eye protection, and face protection.', 'Store in a well-ventilated place. Keep container tightly closed. Store locked up.', NULL, 'IF EXPOSED: Call poison center. IF IN EYES: Rinse with water immediately.', 'Store in a well-ventilated place. Keep container tightly closed. Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local, regional, national, and international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not regulated', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039', NULL, NULL, '1 year', NULL, NULL, NULL,
