  ) VALUES (
    'SpecPoxy Sealer (Part A)', 'specpoxy-sealer-part-a', 'Penetrating epoxy sealer for concrete surfaces', 'Scellant époxy pénétrant pour surfaces en béton', 'Sellador epóxico penetrante para superficies de concreto', 'SpecPoxy Sealer is a high-solids, two-component low viscosity penetrating epoxy sealer designed to protect new and existing concrete against deicing salts and chemical attack. SpecPoxy Sealer penetrates into the concrete pores to form a sub-surface seal that resists the penetration of liquid contaminants, chloride ions, and chemicals. Its low viscosity also makes it an excellent crack healer/sealer for many deteriorated concrete surfaces.Actual VOC = 345 grams per liter.
70% SOLIDS PENETRATING EPOXY SEALER', 'Surface Preparation: New concrete must be a minimum of 21-28 days old with all curing compounds and sealers removed. The concrete must be clean, dry, and sound. All oil, dirt, debris, paint, and unsound concrete must be removed. SpecPoxy Sealer is designed as a penetrating sealer. To ensure proper adhesion to a hard-troweled surface, a test section should be made to determine if additional surface profiling (shotblasting/etching) is required.Mixing: All materials should be conditioned to a temperature of 55°F to 80°F. Mix parts A and B (resin and hardener) separately for one minute using a drill and mixing prop. Then, mix Part A and Part B together for three minutes. The epoxy must be well mixed to ensure proper chemical reaction. Once mixed, immediately apply to the surface.Placement: This product may be applied by squeegee, roller, or industrial sprayer. When applying to seal hairline cracks, flood coat the surface and let the material pool over cracked areas for five minutes to ensure the cracks are filled. Squeegee or broom away any excess material from the surface. For improved skid resistance, broadcast clean, dry silica sand to refusal immediately after excess sealer has been removed from the surface. After the initial cure, remove excess sand. Due to variations in the porosity of concrete surfaces, SpecPoxy Sealer may create an irregular amber appearance if not applied uniformly. If desired, additional coats of this product may be applied after the initial sealer has become tack-free. This can occur as early as six hours but must be within 12 hours of initial placement.
WHMIS Classification: Class B2, D2B', NULL, NULL, '2 years from date of manufacture', '- Avoid application at air and floor temperatures below 50°F.- Store indoors at 45°F to 90°F.- Use in a well-ventilated area.- Keep away from sparks and open flames.- Product may yellow in outdoor (strong sunlight) environments.- Avoid contact with eyes and skin; epoxy components may cause irritation.- Apply only over dry concrete surfaces.- Not designed as a high-build exterior sealer.- Not recommended for new concrete less than 28 days old.- Rubber-wheeled vehicles may leave black tire marks.- If HVAC intake ducts distribute epoxy odor into adjoining occupied areas, take care to block these ventilation vents.', 'Danger', '<p>Bisphenol A Diglycidyl Ether Resin, Aromatic Hydrocarbon, Benzyl Alcohol</p>', 'Causes skin irritation, serious eye irritation. Suspected of causing genetic defects. Flammable liquid and vapour. Toxic to aquatic life with long-lasting effects.', 'Wear protective gloves, eye protection, and face protection. Wash thoroughly after handling. Avoid breathing fumes or dust. Keep away from heat and open flames.', NULL, 'IF ON SKIN: Wash with water. IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses if present and easy to do.', 'Store locked up. Keep in a well-ventilated area.', 'Dispose of contents/container in accordance with local/regional/national/international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Combustible Liquid, n.o.s.', 'UN1993', 'Class 3 - Combustible Liquid', 'PG III', '128', NULL, '<img width="75" height="75" style="width:75px;height:75px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4 alt="Do Not Freeze" class="corner-icon">', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, NULL,
