  ) VALUES (
    'SpecPrime', 'specprime', 'Re-emulsifiable underlayment primer for SpecFlow', 'Apprêt de sous-couche réémulsifiable pour SpecFlow', 'Imprimador de base reemulsionable para niveladores SpecFlow', 'SpecPrime is a ready-to-use, rewettable primer designed to bond new concrete and SpecChem underlayments to horizontal concrete and other sound surfaces. Recommended for interior and dry applications only. Specifically formulated as a primer for SpecFlow.
    
Regulatory Compliance: SCAQMD Rule 1168; Adhesive   Sealant; Actual/Maximum VOC = 0 grams/liter, DO NOT THIN.', 'Use as a primer/bonding agent for underlayments, plaster, and stucco. Surfaces must be clean, structurally sound, and free of water, soluble materials, or contaminants before applying SpecPrime.
    
      Apply SpecPrime at a rate of 100–150 square feet per gallon. Coverage may vary depending on surface porosity. Apply with a brush, broom, or sprayer, and work the material into the surface. Drying time is typically two to three hours at 70°F, and SpecPrime will remain slightly tacky when dry. Remove accumulation in low areas. Use fans to improve air circulation and speed drying.
    
      Under normal conditions, SpecPrime can be applied up to 24 hours before underlayment installation. Keep jobsite traffic to a minimum until the underlayment is installed. For very porous surfaces, two applications may be necessary—allow two to three hours between coats. Reapply if a continuous film is not achieved.', 'Re-emulsifiable for strong bonds with underlayments

Easy application—brush, broom, or spray

Zero VOC—compliant with stringent regulations

Remains tacky to maximize bond with toppings

Ready to use; no thinning required

Ideal for SpecFlow underlayment systems', '100–150 square feet per gallon (varies with surface porosity)', 'Shelf life of SpecPrime in the original, tightly closed container is 1 year from the date of manufacture. Do not allow the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants.', 'Do not allow to freeze.

Do not apply over frozen surfaces, water-soluble paints, rust, or peeling paints.

Do not apply where excessive hydrostatic pressure is present.

Protect SpecPrime film from dirt and other job site contaminants until topping is placed.

Follow all precautions found in SDS, product labels, and technical literature.', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable<p>Non applicable</p>', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', NULL, 'Not applicable', 'None applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable<p>Non applicable</p>', 'Not applicable', '<ul class="statement-list"><li>Not applicable</li></ul>', '<ul class="statement-list"><li>Not applicable</li></ul>', NULL, '<ul class="statement-list"><li>Not applicable</li></ul>', '<ul class="statement-list"><li>None applicable</li></ul>', '<ul class="statement-list"><li>Not applicable</li></ul>', 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', '<img width="72" style="width:72px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039 class="green-conscious-icon" alt="Green Conscious"/>', '<img width="75" height="75" style="width:75px;height:75px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4 alt="Do Not Freeze" class="corner-icon">', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, 'VOC compliant',
