    'SpecShield WB', 'specshield-wb', 'Rewettable PVA latex bonding agent and admixture', 'Agent de liaison en latex PVA réhumectable et additif', 'Agente de adhesión y aditivo de látex PVA rehumectable', 'PLASTER BOND is a rewettable PVA latex bonding agent designed especially for interior/exterior bonding of fresh plaster in patching, plastering, and topping applications. Recommended for interior and/or exterior use not subjected to constant moisture, hydrostatic pressure, or continuous water saturation. Can be used as an admixture to improve the adhesion and durability of interior plaster and plaster mixes to horizontal and vertical surfaces.', 'Surface Preparation: Mechanically abrade the existing substrate to remove all unsound concrete. The substrate must be structurally sound and free of laitance, grease, oil, dirt, or any other contaminants that may adversely affect the bond. The prepared surface must be dust-free and have a sufficient profile to ensure adequate mechanical lock.Mixing and Application Guidelines: Agitate well before use.Bonding Agent: Apply a uniform coating of undiluted PLASTER BOND at 250 sq ft per gallon to the prepared surface by brush, roller, or sprayer. If spray applied, brush or broom into the substrate, forming a continuous film over the entire area to be bonded. The coverage rate varies with the porosity of the surface. Drying time is 20-30 minutes at 70°F. PLASTER BOND will remain slightly tacky when dry. Accumulation in low areas should be wiped up. Poor ventilation will delay normal drying time. Fans will help increase air circulation to speed drying time. Under normal conditions, PLASTER BOND can be applied up to 24 hours before the installation of underlayment toppings. All areas subject to application must be clean of all foreign materials. Traffic should be kept to a minimum. Very porous surfaces will require two applications of Bond-Abell. Allow 1-2 hours between applications. If a continuous film is not achieved on the surface, reapply PLASTER BOND.Place plaster or stucco within 24 hours. The application instructions highlight typical conditions. (When in doubt, always apply a test patch.) Apply undiluted at 250 sq ft/gal, drying time 20-30 mins.', NULL, NULL, 'Shelf life of PLASTER BOND in the original tightly closed container is one year from the date of manufacture. Protect from freezing. Do not allow the accumulation of water, dirt, or other contaminants.', 'Do not allow to freeze. Do not apply over frozen surfaces, water-soluble paints, rust, or peeling paints, or when the temperature is below 40°F. Do not apply where excessive hydrostatic pressure is present. PLASTER BOND is not recommended as a waterproofing agent. Until the topping is placed, protect the PLASTER BOND film from dirt and other job site contaminants. Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Not applicable', 'None', 'None', 'Wear appropriate personal protective clothing to prevent eye and skin contact. Avoid breathing vapors or mists of this product. Use with adequate ventilation. Do not take internally. / Porter des vêtements de protection appropriés pour éviter tout contact avec les yeux et la peau. Éviter d''inhaler les vapeurs ou les brouillards de ce produit. Utiliser avec une ventilation adéquate. Ne pas ingérer.', NULL, 'General information: No special measures required. / Informations générales : Aucune mesure spéciale requise. After inhalation: Supply fresh air; consult doctor in case of complaints. / Après inhalation : Fournir de l''air frais ; consulter un médecin en cas de malaise. After skin contact: If skin irritation continues, consult a doctor. / Après contact avec la peau : Si l''irritation persiste, consulter un médecin. After eye contact: Rinse opened eye for several minutes under running water. If symptoms persist, consult a doctor. / Après contact avec les yeux : Rincer l''œil ouvert pendant plusieurs minutes sous l''eau courante. Si les symptômes persistent, consulter un médecin. After swallowing: If symptoms persist consult doctor. / Après ingestion : Si les symptômes persistent, consulter un médecin.', 'Store in a clean, dry area between 45-85°F (6-29°C). Keep from freezing. / Entreposer dans un endroit propre et sec entre 6 et 29°C. Protéger du gel.', 'Dispose of waste material according to local, state, federal, and provincial environmental regulations. / Éliminer les déchets conformément aux réglementations environnementales locales, provinciales et fédérales.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=f58533a5-5698-4e4e-968b-cd4af2bc2a28', '<img width="75" height="75" style="width:75px;height:75px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fdo-not-freeze.png?alt=media&token=20c12d11-97d2-4863-999c-3a0e08ccfee4 alt="Do Not Freeze" class="corner-icon">', NULL, '2 years', NULL, NULL, 'Actual VOC = 0 grams/liter',
