  ) VALUES (
    'Total Patch', 'total-patch', 'Very rapid setting multi-purpose concrete repair mortar', 'Un mortier de réparation de béton à prise rapide et polyvalent pour des applications à haute résistance initiale', 'Un mortero de reparación de concreto de fraguado rápido y multiusos para aplicaciones de alta resistencia inicial', 'TOTAL PATCH is a very rapid-setting, multi-purpose, rapid-setting concrete repair mortar for use on concrete floors, highway pavements, and other applications requiring high early strength and early resumption of traffic or use. TOTAL PATCH is formulated to meet the requirements of ASTM C928 Packaged, Dry, Rapid Hardening Cementitious Material for Concrete Repair and AASHTO T260. TOTAL PATCH incorporates the latest technology offering superior durability, performance and ease of application without liquid activators for horizontal (featheredge to 4”) and vertical form & pour applications.', 'Depending on the application and area dimensions, TOTAL PATCH can be applied in applications from a feather edge to 4” without extension. Consult SpecChem tech service for further details.

Deep Applications
For DOT and heavy traffic applications (roadways, parking structures, etc) over 2”, TOTAL PATCH should be extended with clean, SSD, 3/8” aggregate up to 60% by weight (30lbs). Choose a clean (free of organic material) well-graded 3/8” aggregate. Aggregate should be pre-dampened prior to mixing with TOTAL PATCH. The total mixing water for the batch shall be reduced by the amount of free water found in the aggregate. 60% extension will add approx. 0.18 cu-ft to the unit yield. Thoroughly mixed product should be placed within 5-6 min.

Placement
Trowel, or screed TOTAL PATCH firmly into the prepared area, ensuring intimate contact with the bonding surface. Finish TOTAL PATCH level with the surrounding concrete and allow to take an initial set. After the initial set, when TOTAL PATCH is surface hard, finish by hand trowelling. Excessive troweling is not required.', '• One-component, dry-polymer, Just add water.
• Easy-to-use, flowable consistency
• Air entrained for excellent freeze-thaw durability
• Suitable for horizontal and formed vertical application
• Takes traffic in 1 hour after set (at 73°F)
• Feather edge to 4” without extension', NULL, 'Shelf life of unopened bags stored in a dry facility is 12 months. Excessive temperature differential and/or high humidity can shorten the shelf life expectancy. Store in a cool, dry area away from direct sunlight.', 'Minimum thickness for horizontal repairs subjected to heavy or severe traffic is 1/2”. Do not retemper after initial mixing. Do not add other cements or additives to this product. TOTAL PATCH is a fast setting product, so mixing equipment should be cleaned with water as soon as possible. Use only potable water for mixing.
Application range 40°F to 90°F. Please consult SpecChem for special instructions on any application outside this temperature range.
Adverse Weather Application: In adverse temperatures, follow ACI recommendations for hot/cold weather concreting practices. For optimum results, condition bagged material to between 65°F and 85°F overnight.
Cold Weather applications should follow procedures outlined in ACI 306. Conditioning the material before mixing to 65°F and 85°F, heating the repair area, using warm water for mixing, and tenting or insulating the patch area after application will increase strength development. Do not use direct, unvented heat on the patch after installation. Do not allow repairs to freeze until the material has reached a minimum of 1000 psi compressive strength.
Caution: Contains Portland cement and sand. Cement will cause irritation. Avoid contact. A dust respirator, safety goggles, and rubber gloves are recommended. Avoid prolonged contact with clothing. In case of contact with eyes, immediately flush with water for at least 15 minutes. Get prompt medical attention. Do not wear contact lenses when working with this product. DO NOT take internally. Keep out of reach of children.
Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheet (SDS), product labels, and technical literature. Please read this information prior to using the product.', 'Danger', '<p>Crystalline Silica (Quartz), Portland Cement, Calcium Oxide</p>', 'Causes serious eye damage, skin irritation, and respiratory issues.', 'Wear gloves, eye protection, and respirator.', NULL, 'IF ON SKIN: Wash with water. IF IN EYES: Rinse with water.', 'Store in a cool, dry area.', 'Dispose in accordance with local regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not regulated', '<img width="72" style="width:72px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039 class="green-conscious-icon" alt="Green Conscious"/>', NULL, NULL, '1 year', NULL, NULL, NULL,
