  ) VALUES (
    'UW Admixture', 'uw-admixture', 'A powder admixture that minimizes washout and improves bond strength when placed underwater', 'Adjuvant en poudre qui minimise le lessivage et améliore la résistance d’adhérence lors de la pose sous l’eau', 'Aditivo en polvo que minimiza el lavado y mejora la resistencia de unión bajo el agua', 'SpecChem UW Admixture is a powder admixture that, when added to Portland cement or mortar, minimizes washout when placed underwater. It also improves the bond strength of fresh concrete to submerged concrete and steel, while reducing bleeding and segregation in the mix. The product creates a stiffer, more thixotropic concrete that is still easy to place using pumping or vibration methods.', 'Mix Ratio: Add 1 - 20 lb. Pail per cubic yard of concrete at the jobsite into ready-mix truck. Mix completely for 5 to 10 minutes or until a lump free homogeneous consistency is achieved.
Note: Addition rates for SpecChem UW Admixture are based on a 5.5 - 6.0 bag cement mix. Use super plasticizer as required to achieve an approximate w/c ratio of .40 - .45 with a 3-4 slump. When properly mixed the concrete mix will appear to have a stiff consistency, but flow easily by inducing any pressure or force (i.e. vibration or pumping).
Placing: Mixed concrete should be placed to minimize any free drop through water and should be placed in a continuous process. A tremie process provides optimum results. Keep the discharge tube submerged in the fresh concrete whenever possible.', NULL, NULL, 'Shelf life of unopened pails stored in a dry facility is 12 months from batch date. Store in a cool, dry area away from direct sunlight.', 'Overwatering the mix can reduce anti-washout performance. Avoid hazards by following all precautions in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Danger', '<p>Crystalline Silica, Portland Cement, Naphthalene</p>', 'Suspected of causing cancer. May cause damage to organs (respiratory system) through prolonged or repeated exposure. May cause respiratory irritation. Causes skin irritation. May cause an allergic skin reaction. Causes serious eye damage.', 'Obtain special instructions before use. Avoid breathing dust, fumes, or spray. Wear protective gloves, eye protection, and face protection.', NULL, 'IF INHALED: Remove to fresh air, seek medical attention if unwell. IF IN EYES: Rinse thoroughly with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses if present.', 'Store in a cool, dry area away from direct sunlight and moisture.', 'Dispose of contents/container per local regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', NULL, NULL, NULL, '18 months', NULL, NULL, NULL,
