  ) VALUES (
    'UW Grout', 'uw-grout', 'A pumpable underwater, non-shrink cement-based grout for underwater repair applications', 'Un coulis cimentaire non-rétractable et pompable pour les réparations sous-marines', 'Un mortero bombeable sin contracción a base de cemento para aplicaciones de reparación submarina', 'UW Grout is a pumpable, underwater, non-shrink cement-based grout designed for use in underwater repair applications, such as pile restoration. It is formulated to resist washout in underwater conditions, making it ideal for applications in tidal zones. UW Grout can be used in thicknesses from 1/2" to several inches. The grout is resistant to saltwater and is designed for minimal washout.', 'Mixing Instructions: Air, material, and surface temperatures must be a minimum of 40°F prior to mixing or installation. To assist with mixing and dispensing, precondition material to 75°F. Mix one part of Part A and one part of Part B by volume for three minutes with a low speed heavy-duty drill and a Jiffy mixer in a separate 5 gal pail. Add the mixed epoxy to a mortar mixer for mixing larger units, slowly adding Part C (aggregate) and mixing for an additional 2-3 minutes. Maximum yield is achieved by mixing in all the Part C aggregate. Always mix full complete units.
High Flow Applications: Reduce the amount of Part C aggregate up to 25% by weight to create a more fluid grout consistency for difficult high flow placements.
Surface Preparation: Surfaces to be grouted must be clean, and structurally sound. Remove all oil, grease, dirt, laitance, and any other foreign matter and profile the surface by sandblasting, mechanical abrasion removing any residue with pressure washer or an oil free compressed air.
Placing: The mixed grout should be poured continuously and in such a manner as to provide full and complete contact within the void or annulus to be filled. Strapping will facilitate moving the grout into position. Grout should be placed at a minimum of 1.0” thick up to a maximum of 18” thick per lift in a large mass. Full aggregate extension must be used for large applications in excess of 6” deep. Anchor bolt holes should be dry and free of all contaminants.', NULL, NULL, 'One year in original unopened packaging when stored in dry conditions.', 'Do not exceed the recommended water amount. Follow ACI recommendations for hot/cold weather concreting practices. Use potable water for mixing. Minimum temperature for application is 45°F and rising. Clean equipment immediately after use. Avoid hazards by following all precautions found in the Safety Data Sheets (SDS), product labels, and technical literature.', 'Danger', '<p>Crystalline Silica (Quartz), Portland Cement, Naphthalene, Fly Ash</p>', 'Suspected of causing cancer. May cause damage to organs (respiratory system) through prolonged or repeated exposure. Causes skin irritation. Causes serious eye damage.', 'Obtain special instructions before use. Wear protective gloves, eye protection, and face protection. Do not breathe dust, fume, gas, mist, vapors, or spray.', NULL, 'IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses if present and easy to do. Immediately call a POISON CENTER or doctor. IF ON SKIN: Wash with plenty of water. If skin irritation occurs, seek medical advice.', 'Store in a well-ventilated place. Keep container tightly closed. Store locked up.', 'Dispose of contents and container in accordance with local, regional, national, and international regulations.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Not regulated', 'Not regulated', 'Not regulated', 'Not regulated', 'Not regulated', '<img width="72" style="width:72px;object-fit:contain;" src=https://firebasestorage.googleapis.com/v0/b/specchem-pwa-feb-25.firebasestorage.app/o/pictograms%2Fgreen-conscious.png?alt=media&token=1337ae3b-9ed9-4956-8d2f-fc958810c039 class="green-conscious-icon" alt="Green Conscious"/>', NULL, NULL, '1 year', NULL, NULL, NULL,
