- Polymer-modified for enhanced performance
- Fiber-reinforced formulation
- Meets industry shotcrete standards', 'Remove all loose deteriorated or contaminated concrete to sound substrate. Clean surface thoroughly with high-pressure water blast or other approved methods. Pre-wet surface thoroughly and maintain in saturated surface dry condition during application. Load SPECSHOT into pneumatic equipment hopper. Adjust water pressure and volume at nozzle for proper consistency. Begin application at lowest point and work upward. Apply in continuous passes to build required thickness.', 'Rapid-setting dry shotcrete mix, Excellent adhesion and low rebound, High early and ultimate strength, Suitable for vertical and overhead applications, Polymer-modified for enhanced performance, Fiber-reinforced formulation, Meets industry shotcrete standards', 'Can be applied from 1/2 inch to 6 inches in a single pass. For thicker applications apply in multiple passes allowing each to reach initial set.', 'Store in original packages in a dry location off the ground. Protect from moisture. The shelf life of properly stored SPECSHOT is one year from the date of manufacture.', 'Requires skilled shotcrete operator for proper application. Equipment must be properly calibrated for consistent results. Do not add admixtures unless approved by manufacturer. Material has limited working time once wetted. Rebound material should not be reused. INDUSTRIAL USE ONLY.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Store in dry conditions. Keep container tightly closed. Protect from moisture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,
