    category_id, sort_order, is_active
  ) VALUES (
    'IntraHard', 'intrahard', 'Blended Silicate Concrete Sealer/Densifier/Hardener', 'Scellant/Densificateur/Durcisseur de béton à base de silicate', 'Sellador/Densificador/Endurecedor de concreto a base de silicato', 'INTRAHARD is a premium blended silicate sealer/densifier/hardener for concrete surfaces. The unique proprietary blend of silicates reacts to produce a calcium silicate hydrate within the concrete pores. INTRAHARD''s blend of silicates allows a breathable surface while providing reduced porosity, dusting, and water permeability while increasing abrasion resistance. IntraHard provides a more complete densification process ideally suited for Type 1L cement concrete mix designs.', 'Always apply INTRAHARD to a clean surface free of cures, bond breakers, oil, dirt, grease or debris. Application for freshly placed concrete: After final finishing apply with a low pressure sprayer with a fan tip. Uniformly spread with a soft broom or microfiber applicator to thoroughly coat the concrete eliminating any puddles or excess. Keep the surface wet for approximately 15 minutes. Apply additional INTRAHARD to porous areas until rejection. Remove excess from the surface with a squeegee, power sweeper, or floor scrubbing machine. Application as pre-seal densifier for tilt-up: after INTRAHARD has dried, apply an extra application of compatible curing compound/bondbreaker. Application for existing concrete or polishable overlays: Clean/open the surface (e.g., 100-grit screen), rinse and allow to dry; apply a single saturating coat, spread uniformly, and let dry. Typical dry time 1–2 hours.', 'Reduce application costs with one-step low pressure spray application. Achieve architectural finishes; does not contribute to ASR. Reduces dusting, porosity, and water permeability. Improves abrasion resistance, light reflectance, stain resistance, and gloss. Breathable; interior/exterior. Fast-curing; ready for traffic in about one hour. Apply on new or existing concrete. Environment